## Implementation Fix: scan_vault_feed dot-file / symlink exclusion (FIND-S5-CONTRACT-004)

### Before (feed.rs:404-408, Sprint 5 iter-1):
```rust
for entry in read_dir.flatten() {
    let file_path = entry.path();
    if file_path
        .extension()
        .is_some_and(|ext| ext.eq_ignore_ascii_case("md"))
    {
```
No dot-file filter. No file_type() check. Symlinks would be followed.

### After (feed.rs:404-422, Sprint 5 contract-fix):
```rust
for entry in read_dir.flatten() {
    let file_path = entry.path();
    // Sprint 5 vault scan semantics (REQ-FEED-028 / FIND-S5-SPEC-011):
    // - exclude dot-files (dot-prefixed file name)
    if file_path
        .file_name()
        .and_then(|n| n.to_str())
        .is_some_and(|n| n.starts_with('.'))
    {
        continue;
    }
    // - exclude symlinks and non-regular files (is_file() is false for symlinks in Rust std)
    if !entry.file_type().is_ok_and(|ft| ft.is_file()) {
        continue;
    }
    if file_path
        .extension()
        .is_some_and(|ext| ext.eq_ignore_ascii_case("md"))
    {
```
Dot-files skipped. Symlinks (and directories) skipped via file_type().is_file() gate.

## New Cargo Tests Added (FIND-S5-CONTRACT-003)

Added to: promptnotes/src-tauri/tests/feed_handlers.rs

1. test_feed_initial_state_excludes_dot_md_files
   - Creates TempDir with .hidden.md + regular.md
   - Asserts .hidden.md absent from note_metadata and visible_note_ids
   - Asserts regular.md present in note_metadata

2. test_feed_initial_state_excludes_symlink_md_files  [#[cfg(unix)]]
   - Creates TempDir with target.md (real file) + link.md (symlink -> target.md)
   - Asserts link.md absent from note_metadata and visible_note_ids
   - Asserts target.md present in note_metadata

3. test_feed_initial_state_ignores_subdirectory_md_files
   - Creates TempDir with sub/nested.md
   - Asserts sub/nested.md absent (non-recursive scan gate)

